*********************************************************************
****************************	README	  ***************************
*********************************************************************

CoMET is written in PHP, with a lot of support from jQuery. It uses MySQL 
for the database backend, any database that supports views would work with 
some modification. It requires PHP of at least version 5.3 and has been 
tested and designed with MySQL 5. It uses PEAR for Auth and Mail support.

A. General Information
B. Requirements
C. Installation
D. Configuration/Setup
E. Usage
F. Troubleshooting
G. Extending

*********************************************************************
********************	General Information		*********************
*********************************************************************



*********************************************************************
************************	Requirements	*************************
*********************************************************************
- PHP 5.3 or later with mysqli, curl and cli extensions enabled
- MySQL 5 or later
- PEAR packages: Net_SMTP, Mail, Auth, MDB2, MDB2/mysqli
- Access to cron


*********************************************************************
************************	Installation	*************************
*********************************************************************
Untar the comet.tar.gz into a directory within the webroot. Create the
appropriate virtualhost file. Open a web browser to the installed location
and install.php.


*********************************************************************
***********************	Configuration/Setup  ************************
*********************************************************************
The installation script will prompt you for a username, password, and 
email address.


